This is an attempt to use express without any template view. I could start wit a template
just to laydown the folders structur but then I will use plain html and java script without 
view framework (Not really totally possible as of my actual understanding). 

This still uses some ejs so for better undertanding of this see ../ejs-demo folder. 

Let see how it goes.

1.- npm init.
2.- npx express-generator --view=ejs.
3.- make change in the view engine from ejs to html.
4.- change file extension from ejs to html.
5.- TODO: AJAX checar como hacerlo
6.- npm install html
7.- npm install consolidate 
8.- ahcer cambios en el puntos 3: 
	https://stackoverflow.com/questions/16111386/error-cannot-find-module-html-when-visiting-html-page/16111469#16111469	
	https://github.com/tj/consolidate.js
	
	var engines = require('consolidate');
	app.set('views', __dirname + '/views');
	app.engine('html', engines.mustache);
	app.set('view engine', 'html');


lmonhdz@acr-debian:~/MernStack/express/htmlvanilla$ npx express-generator --view=ejs
